ractices—science and exploration—it recovers the stories of women’s contributions that were sometimes accidentally, and sometimes deliberately, erased. Engaging and provocative, this book is a history of the scientists and physiologists who face challenges that are physically demanding, frequently dangerous, and sometimes fatal, in the interest of advancing modern science and pushing the boundaries of human ability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aExtreme environmentsxPhysiological effect. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aacclimatization.  aexploration.  afield.  ahuman experimentation.  aindigenous peoples.  alaboratory.  amaterial culture.  aphysiology.  arace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226650913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226650913.jpg  a978-3-11-061053-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPMb2019